pr_review_comment_body:
@breznak explained what this `id` is for:

> preparation for the next steps. in the minimize= field of permutations.py the MultiMetric cannot be described/constructed by the string, so I want to make it possible to identify the metric by id

What about the other metrics? If `id` is optional, how do you plan to minimize over them?

@zabil Sorry, but I don't understand what do I need to do. :)
What means "modify this pull request to the new location"?
What is "location" of the pull request? Am I made a pull request to incorrect repository - or this is about something else?

@ageorges: shouldn't matter whether vsc-utils touches `vsc/utils` too, vsc-base by itself works just fine when installed as a zipped egg

However, other stuff that requires it as a dep doesn't support using it when it's installed as a zipped egg yet *cough* EasyBuild *cough*

So, for now, Jenkins shouldn't install it as a zipped egg after a successful merge/test, i.e. it should use `easy_install -U`

i believe it would be more clear to construct the result differently in the firstresult case

```python
if firstresult:
   outcome = _Result(results[0] if results else None, excinfo)
else:
  outcome = _Result(results, excinfo)

@Bento007 he's talking about whether \" is allowed inside quoted-string params of media-types.

@ttung Technically, yes \" (a "quoted-pair" per https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7230#section-3.2.6) is allowed.  You really love these technically-correct hyper-obscure corner cases, don't you :)
I'll fix this later.  Right now my priority is getting the DCP integrated, not wasting time implementing code that will never be used.  If you can show me a case where someone has used a quoted-pair on a media-type parameter I'll bump up the priority of this, but frankly even finding cases where people use params is hard.
